This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the task of modeling open-domain, multi-turn, unstructured, multi-participant, conversational dialogue using deep neural networks. The paper also mentions the use of Reddit comments and posts to extract conversational data, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of deep neural networks for training the models suggests the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper focuses on the task of predicting the next response in a conversation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also mentions the incorporation of personalization and history for response ranking, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
